<p>
    <strong>2014 Digital Curriculum Strategy Discussion Meetings</strong>
</p>
<p>
    We work with your district and surrounding schools to invite 7-14 executive rank attendees who are comprised of the leadership of the district, the
    schools, curriculum and instruction, and I.T. We want to keep the meeting highly conversational and “working.” Neighboring districts are also invited.
</p>
<p>
    At the Discussion, a special intro by The Learning Counsel on the state-of-developments in curriculum trends nationally kicks off the day. We’ll give a
    day’s discussion assignment for the executive attendees in the morning for note-taking during the presentations.
</p>
<p>
    For part of the morning and early afternoon, we will have a “provocateur” to lead attendees in discussions with each other and through half-hour
    presentations by several digital curriculum publisher sponsors on topics related to digital curriculum. These presentations get the “wheels turning” for
    what’s current in the industry.
</p>
